  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to curricular reform in Croatia - Phase 4</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Ministry of Science and Education of Republic of Croatia 
The National Centre for External Evaluation of Education 
The Education and Teacher Training Agency 
The Croatian Academic and Research Network (CARNET); experts working on final tests (Matura), advisors and mentors supporting teachers.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the project is to contribute towards the successful implementation of curricular reform in Croatia.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The three outcomes are: Croatian assessment experts and mentors develop a better understanding of how assessment of learning can align with the learning outcomes set in the new curriculum. 

Croatian assessment experts are prepared to design assessment of learning outcomes in Matura, and mentors are prepared to support teachers in designing and developing quality assessment of learning. 

Officials at the Ministry and the National Centre for External Evaluation of Education are advised on reforming the system of external assessment, including on preparing for e-assessment.</narrative>
  </description>
